text:
Rustic village atmosphere but come prepared to handle the mosquitoes.

Nasi lemak 👍 nice sambal
Murtabak beef 👍
Roti cinai 🫲 dough too dense but lovely fish curry
Longtong kering 🫲
Mee soto 👎
Teh tarik 👎 dilute

An awesome kampung warung!! Dont be deceived by the outlook of the warong..

The food.. esp the roti canai sarang burung, with the dhal n cili gravy, simply kampung awesome..

Had a look at the mee goreng ordered by the next table.. decided to try.. simply kampung awesome..

Love the kampung warong ambience.. yes, trees all around and durian trees included..

No issue with parking as long u dont cover the kampung road passing by it la...

N its so near to Linkedua.. tak ke gerek@isn't that cool for Singies
Kampung style... the roti and kuah dhal.. superb.. try la.. many cyclist often eat here..

Roti canai,soto nasi,lontong basah/kering is a must try here. Nasi lemak always sold out before 8.30am,havent try cause always reach here around 9am. Will come again earlier. Reccommended to breakfast here before go to Pendas fish market for fresh seafood.
"Roti Canai" in specific served by order for breakfast.Alternative "Pit" stop for early bird cyclists to Pendas before heading to Tanjung Piai/Kukup unless you have ample suppliment.
